lighttpd rewrite rules match against the full url-path + query-string, whereas `$HTTP[&quot;url&quot;]` is just the url-path (yes, I can see how that can be a bit confusing) and `$HTTP[&quot;query-string&quot;]` is just the query-string.

The following uses some syntax available in lighttpd 1.4.50 (released over a year ago)  The current version of lighttpd is lighttpd 1.4.54.  (If you&#39;re using, say, lightttpd 1.4.45, your distro is, uhhh, more than a tad behind)

    $HTTP[&quot;url&quot;] !~ &quot;^/(dashboard|admin)/&quot; {
        url.access-deny = (&quot;&quot;)
    }
    $HTTP[&quot;url&quot;] !~ &quot;\.(?i:gif|png|jpe?g|bmp|css|js|swf|wav|avi|mpg|ttf|woff)$&quot; {
        url.rewrite-if-not-file = (
            &quot;^(/.*)\.sa(\?.*)?$&quot; =&gt; &quot;index.php?sa=$1${qsa}&quot;,
            &quot;&quot; =&gt; &quot;/index.php?uri=${url.path}${qsa}&quot;,
        )
    }
    server.follow-symlink = &quot;enable&quot;

